It's International Podcast Day!! When I started podcasting, I never imagined people would interested in what I have to say, so I made the decision to share the stories of others instead of my own.

Because of that, I've been able to meet with and talk to some of the most amazing creators and share their stories with all of you.

The highlight of my long weekend would have to be getting this setup. An actual (original) Super Nintendo gaming console with a few cool games. ⠀
⠀
I also had a bit of time to delve into the world that is "retro gaming" and wow...there's a lot I didn't know about. It's a completely new sub-culture I didn't even know about and trying to acquire some of these games is surprisingly a more expensive hobby than I first thought. Definitely, more research required for that. I also need to find a cool way to store and display it all (if anyone's got suggestions, DM me!)⠀
⠀
It's somewhat ironic and yet mindblowing that I'm taking this picture with my iPhone which has so much computational power in comparison to the SNES...which has even more computational power than what got humans to the moon. It’s humbling when you look at it in terms of technological advancements and evolution.⠀
⠀

caption.text:
DEFENDERS OF THE EARTH: Here's the UK magazine advert for the excellent home computer game based on the awesome cartoon show from the 80's.

Released for the ZX Spectrum, Commodore 64, Amstrad CPC, Amiga and Atari ST this was a great action game that went very much under the radar at the time. So many games based on cartoon shows back in the day were awful but this one is very good.

caption.text:
BIONIC COMMANDO: In 1987 arcade gamers became special forces soldiers in order to infiltrate an enemy base and stop the launch of a devastating missile attack.

A classic action platform game from Capcom this is one of the coolest games of its time thanks to all jumping being removed in favour of using an extendable arm to move around the level.

Converted to a ton of home computers including the Amiga, Atari ST, C64, ZX Spectrum and Amstrad CPC this also came to the NES although that version was very different. 
Did you ever play this game? caption.text:
LANA DEL REY A.K.A. ELIZABETH GRANT PARTE 1 por @eu.filomena

Não é de hoje que Elizabeth Wooldrige Grant busca expressar suas singularidades e emoções através de composições e arranjos musicais. O primeiro material da musa a que tivemos intitula-se "Sirens" e é assinado pelo alterego May Jailer. Posteriormente, conhecemos Lizzy Grant ao conseguir se associar a uma gravadora, aos poucos transformar-se-ia na persona em que Elizabeth encontrou-se permanente, a deusa @lanadelrey.

Houveram muitas polêmicas em torno dessa transição, já que as mudanças também afetaram na estética de Lana. Contudo, embora saibamos que essas mudanças foram intencionais, não deveríamos nos importar tanto com o preenchimento labial da deusa nem de ninguém, não é mesmo? Portanto, vamos nos atentar à composição do novo nome da musa. Inicialmente grafado Lana Del Ray, o pseudônimo é uma homenagem tanto à atriz norte-americana Lana Turner quanto aos amigos cubanos dos tempos de Miami de Lana D. Rey e a um famoso carro dos anos 80, o Ford Del Rey.

Além do EP "Kill Kill", da transição de Lizzy Grant para Lana Del Rey, surgiu o álbum "Lana Del Ray a.k.a. Lizzy Grant", contabilizando 13 faixas, mas que logo foi retirado de circulação pela própria Lana Del Rey após romper com a gravadora. Fato é que, desde seus primeiros trabalhos, Elizabeth sempre tratou de uma persona triste e fragilizada ao mesmo tempo que apaixonada e dependente de seus amores sob uma estética vintage.

Factualmente, o álbum de estreia da cantora devidamente rebatizada Lana Del Rey, chamado "Born To Die", consolida as veias melancólicas e problemáticas do primeiro "hit" da cantora, "Video Games". Contudo, acredita-se que Lana Del Rey tenha atingido o ápice da melancolia no álbum "Ultraviolence", que traz problemáticas com álcool e relacionamentos abusivos. Esses ares autodestrutivos da diva perduraram até depois de "Honeymoon", com o lançamento de "Lust For Life" em 2017.

É como se, após tantos anos, Lana começasse a dar sinais de renascimento e superação, deixando sua força se consolidar em "Norman Fucking Rockwell", lançado em agosto deste ano e sobre o qual de fato trataremos na segunda parte desta coluna.

He’s willing to get involved at a personal level that most Jedi among his peers ignored. Obi-Wan was human in a way the other Jedi were not, this story is about Obi-Wan as a person, a man, a grieved man, a man who never gives up, a man who takes care of others selflessly, a man who holds onto who he is even when no one is watching or when it’s really hard. He is capable of seeing the potential in people and tries to bring that out. He’s charming and funny, and is really responsible for some of the brightest and best moments in the saga. caption.text:
👨🏻‍🦰 #Bobbys31DaysOfHorror
🎃
If you know me, have been following my page and/or my newest followers then you (should) know I love all things horror. Last year I covered 31 videos games for the month of October. Halloween is my favorite holiday right next to X-mas and since I got a lot of good feed back last year I figured why not do it again!
🦇
I do not have any special criteria on how I picked the games, just that I played them all. If it's gory, creepy, extremely violent, ghosts, hauntings, horror themed or psychological, it's all horror to me. Yes there might be more than one game in a franchise and that's ok, if I liked it then it made my list. The games and posts will be random because I didn't want to give a top ten or in this case thirty one games. There will not be a game from last year on this new list.
🔪
The 31 games from last year are
Dead by Daylight • Night Slashers • Univited • Metro Redux • Ghouls 'N Ghost • Castlevania: Symphony of the Night • The Thing • Dead Nation • Resident Evil 4 • Maniac Mansion • Dante's Inferno • Castlevania • Silent Hill 2 • Monster Party • Parasite Eve • Deadly Premonition • Medievil (PS1) • The Suffering • Friday the 13th (NES) • Bloodborne • Zombies Ate My Neighbors • Resident Evil • Manhunt • Until Dawn • Nosferatu • Evil Dead: A Fistful of Boom Stick • Clocktower • Splatterhouse (TG-16) • Sweet Home • A Nightmare of Elm Street • Outlast
👻
I loved playing horror games in the darkness and with the TV loud but let me tell you, it's wrong. I have played new games and old games using headphones and let me till you it really ups the scare factor by far. Hearing things you couldn't hear before, creepy foot steps or whispers directly into your ear is something that you just need to experience alone in the dark! So tomorrow we kick it off with "Condemned: Criminal Origins"

Depois de ser apresentado na E3 de 2018, os fãs esperavam ansiosos por esse game, que busca uma nova abordagem de gameplay e promete envolver até quem não é fã dessa franquia na trama e nas batalhas que vão além das estrelas. O game se passa depois do Episódio 3 - A vingança de Sith. Sendo um dos últimos Jedi existentes logo após os acontecimentos da ORDEM 66 (Evento que iniciou o expurgo da ORDEM JEDI), Cal Kestis precisa sobreviver e lutar contra o império galático. O game está previsto para sair em 15 novembro para PC, Xbox one e Ps4. Se você quiser conferir um pouco do que está por vir, passe no canal da Playstation no YouTube é confira o trailer!! "Que a força esteja com você!!" 🖖🏼 E não deixe de seguir a @99fichas para ficar por dentro do mundo dos games 🎮

caption.text:
Febbraio 2018: ritratto di una studentessa stanca e pendolare che si gode uno sprazzo di sole invernale in uno splendido parco di Reggio Emilia. Stavo seguendo le ultime lezioni frontali per il percorso di formazione insegnanti e contemporaneamente scrivendo la tesi e facendo avanti e indietro tra Modena e Parma per questioni burocratiche. Valgono le mie occhiaie come testimoni oculari di quanto ho dichiarato?

Nostalgia a parte, dedico questo ricordo a tutti gli studenti, dalla primaria all'università, che ogni giorno affrontano mezzi pubblici, tomi di milioni di pagine ed ore su ore di lezioni. Anche quando vorreste farcire il muro di testate, dare fuoco agli zaini e fucilare i vostri professori, ricordate sempre che vince chi la dura, non chi si arrende!
E concludo dicendo che se ce l'ho fatta io, che sono la pigrizia fatta a donna, ce la possono fare tutti😂.
Buona fortuna, sempre e comunque. E buono studio!
.
.
.

Within a week of it launching the 
Nintendo Switch Lite has already been added to the class action lawsuit against Nintendo regarding “joycon drift”

. "Despite knowing about the Joy-Con defect, Nintendo continues to market and sell the Switch and Joy-Con controllers... without disclosing the defect,"
.

If the Brawl is rooted into an ancient tradition from the past, the idea of the Spirits of Brawl is quite young, and it’s related with Coalington’s urban development.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Coalington was a young city but, despite their different origins, its inhabitants were already blending together, creating a strong social tissue. That was the moment when the primal core of the Spirits of Brawl’s belief came to light.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It wasn't a big cult, as in fact it never tried to be. It was more a sort of philosophy that stuck its hands into myth, mystic and supernatural.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It all began, as you might realize, when a bunch of supporters started wondering about the brawler’s longevity and the reasons behind it. After a bit of logic nonsense, it was Garland Teliéh, an old Macaquiño, who first asked “What if there’s something that protects them? Something above us, something bigger and powerful and plural…”.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
They weren’t “the Spirits of Brawl” at the time, they were only “Them”, and their followers were only a very small percentage of the population. There was no ritualism involved, not at all, only some gratitude at the end of each match for the Brawlers to be still alive. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But then... ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

caption.text:
Every once in a while I lay awake at night, thinking about how criminally underrated Radiant Historia is. 
It is such an incredibly beautiful game, with a good story, unique gameplay and an amazing soundtrack by Yoko Shimomura.
It is so unlike any other Atlus game, it really is a shame they never properly advertised it. The original DS version never even released in Europe and only had a very small print run super late in the DS life cycle. The 3DS remake has new art (tho personally, I prefer the more unique art of the original), a new storyline and full voice acting. While it did release in Europe, the print run was pretty small from what I can tell and there was little to no advertising for it :( Aaand it released way too late in the 3DS life cycle again, so it never had its chance to shine properly :(
